The paper discusses a computer simulation model of pedestrian movement, which involves modeling the behavior of individual pedestrians. This falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) as it involves modeling the behavior of multiple agents (pedestrians) and their interactions. The model also has practical applications in the design of pedestrian areas and evacuation from buildings, which falls under the category of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The model also considers the interaction between pedestrians and obstacles, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the numerical solution of the model, which falls under the category of Scientific Computing (cs.SI).
